FOOT & MOUTH DISEASE - CHINA (05): (GUANGXI ZHUANG) SEROTYPE O, SWINE, OIE
**************************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Sat 21 Apr 2018
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly disease information 2018; 31(17) [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=26466


Foot-and-mouth disease, China (People's Rep of)
-----------------------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 21 Apr 2018 from Dr Zhang Zhongqui, Director General, China Animal Disease Control Centre, Veterinary Bureau, Ministry of Agriculture, Beijing, China (People's Rep. of)

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 11 Apr 2018
Date of confirmation of the event: 16 Apr 2018
Report date: 21 Apr 2018
Date submitted to OIE: 21 Apr 2018
Reason for notification: new strain of a listed disease
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: Foot and mouth disease virus
Serotype: O
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (basic and advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of the outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1: Cenxi City, [Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region]
Date of start of the outbreak: 11 Apr 2018
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: slaughterhouse
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Swine / 51 / 15 / 0 / 51 / 0

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / morbidity rate / mortality rate / case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Swine/ 29.41 / 0 / 0 / 100
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive

Control measures
Measures applied: Movement control inside the country, quarantine, official destruction of animal products, official disposal of carcasses, by-products and waste, disinfection; vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists); no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: Lanzhou National Reference Laboratory Foot and Mouth Disease (OIE reference laboratory)
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Swine / gene sequencing / 16 Apr 2018 / Positive
Swine/ reverse transcription-polymerase chain reaction (RT-PCR) / 16 Apr 2018 / Positive

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map at the source URL above.]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[In addition to this new event, during 2018, China reported another 5 events associated with FMDV serotypes A and O. The situation for each of these events is as follows:

1. Event of 2 Jan 2018: one outbreak reported in Guizhou province. FMDV serotype A was identified. The event is still continuing. See event summary and updated map: http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review/viewsummary?fupser=&dothis=&reportid=25612

2. Event of 3 Jan 2018: one outbreak reported in Guizhou province. FMDV serotype O was identified. The event is still continuing. See event summary and updated map:
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review/viewsummary?fupser=&dothis=&reportid=25614

3. Event of 10 Jan 2018: one outbreak reported in Ningxia province. FMDV serotype O was identified. The event is still continuing. See event summary and updated map: http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review/viewsummary?fupser=&dothis=&reportid=25789

4. Event of 24 Feb 2018: one outbreak reported in Henan province. FMDV serotype O was identified. The event is still continuing. See event summary and updated map:
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review/viewsummary?fupser=&dothis=&reportid=26061

5. Event of 22 Mar 2018: 2 outbreaks have been reported in Gansu and Xinjiang provinces. FMDV serotype O was identified. The event is still continuing. See event summary and updated map: http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review/viewsummary?fupser=&dothis=&reportid=26418
- Mod.CRD

Maps of China: http://www.chinatoday.com/city/MAP_0000.JPG and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5766065,35548]
